Edition:
Quote:  Joe could see i was lost, and explained that a konake is like a sledge, only it has two wide wheels almost at the back and when the horse pulls it lifts the front and the load runs on the wheels. On downhill grades the runners drop and act as a brake. A very simple and efficient vehicle.
