Date:  0/4/1942
Source:  NZ Journal of Agriculture
Author:
Vol / Page:  270
Edition:
Quote:  The konaki is a partly wheeled and partly runnered vehicle... The konaki has replaced the ordinary farm sledge on many farms in Taranaki. The name konaki is apparently derived from the Maori "Ko neke," meaning to slide, crawl or move from one place to another.
